devdoc.details: Contract for recording ship arrival events from RabbitMQ

constructor.details: Constructor sets up the contract with ownership

returns._0: The unique identifier for the event

getPortEvents(string).details: Gets all event IDs for a port

params.portId: The port ID to look up

getRecorder().details: Returns the address that recorded this event

getShipArrival(uint256).details: Gets a ship arrival by ship ID

params._numeroAvis: The ship ID to look up

getShipEvents(string).details: Gets all event IDs for a ship

params.shipId: The ship ID to look up

getStatus().details: Returns the status of the event

getTimestamp().details: Returns the timestamp when the event was recorded on chain

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

recordShipArrival(uint256,string,string,.details: Records a new ship arrival event on the blockchain

params.etat: Current status of the ship arrival (e.g., "EXPECTED", "ARRIVED")

returns._0: eventId The ID of the recorded event

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

shipArrivalExists(uint256).details: Checks if a ship arrival exists for a ship ID

returns._0: True if a ship arrival exists, false otherwise

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

updateShipArrival(uint256,string,string,.details: Updates an existing ship arrival's arrival times

params._etat: New status of the ship arrival
params._numeroAvis: The ship ID of the ship arrival to update
